-- Regression test: exhaustiveness checking over the builtin MAYBE type.
-- NOTHING/JUST live in `entityInfo` as `KnownTerm _ Constructor` (a complete
-- set), so — like BOOLEAN and unlike LIST, whose `cons` is not a plain
-- constructor — MAYBE is exhaustiveness-checked. This match omits NOTHING and
-- must be flagged at type-check time rather than crashing at eval.
GIVEN m IS A MAYBE NUMBER
GIVETH A NUMBER
`unwrap` MEANS
  CONSIDER m
    WHEN JUST x THEN x
